  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5103",
  "title": "Calling `setUiState` directly does not trigger `onStateChange` when defined.",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nWhen calling `setUiState` directly, if `onStateChange` is defined, it does not get called. The state gets properly updated, but the handler is not triggered, even though a state change occurred.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/bold-sunset-k7giog?file=/src/app.js\r\n\r\n- Type something or filter using the facets to set the state to something other than the default value.\r\n- Click the added button which will reset the state using `setUiState` manually.\r\n- Note that the `onStateChange` function does not get called (nothing in the console).\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWhen calling `setUiState` directly (e.g. via a button click or change), the `onStateChange` handler should get called if it's defined.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- OS Mac Monterey 12.5.1\r\n- Browser: Chrome\r\n- Version: 4.44\r\n\r\n## Known Workaround\r\n\r\nUsing a middleware `.onStateChange` will get called.",
